<p class="page" id="a7661090">[Page 90]</p>
<p>All ripping good books, &amp; moreover ones that leave a clean taste in your mouth &ndash; somewhat of a rarity in present day fiction.</p>
<p>I shall have much to talk over and tell you when we meet, and shall much enjoy coming round some of the Concentration Camps with you, if you will allow it.</p>
<p>C. Macnaghten</p>
<p>We expect to sail on Saturday 27th - &amp; should arrive soon after this note.  The ship is the Itonus on which I came back to Alex. after the landing, &amp; which was a veritable shambles.</p>
